      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 19.2) is a commercially validated code with documented QA procedures including version control, regression testing, and release notes. Software QA documentation was reviewed and confirmed compliant with MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Code verification was performed using canonical benchmark cases including lid-driven cavity and backward-facing step flows. Results matched published reference solutions within accepted tolerances, confirming correct implementation of governing equations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA centrifugal pump geometry. Grid convergence index (GCI) was computed following Celik et al. (2008). The fine-grid GCI for hemolysis index was below 3%, meeting MRL 2 discretization error requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions from the FDA interlaboratory study were replicated in simulation: inlet flow rates of 2.5 and 5.0 L/min, impeller speeds of 2500 and 3500 RPM, and blood analog fluid properties at 37°C. Boundary conditions were set to match reported experimental values."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Predicted hemolysis index values were compared against experimental measurements from three independent laboratories. Mean absolute relative error was 18% across all operating points, within the acceptable range for MRL 2 given inherent inter-laboratory variability in hemolysis measurements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest — the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) — is directly relevant to the clinical question of red blood cell damage under CPB conditions. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) support mechanistic interpretation and are standard metrics in pump hemolysis literature."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry as the device under assessment — under flow conditions spanning the intended CPB operating envelope. This direct correspondence between validation and intended use supports the relevance claim at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required for MRL 2; default level 1 is acceptable.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error beyond discretization error (e.g., iterative convergence errors, round-off) is not required to be formally assessed at MRL 2. Residuals were monitored and confirmed to reach steady-state convergence criteria, providing informal assurance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required for MRL 2; default level 1 is acceptable.",
      "rationale": "Formal use error assessment is not required at MRL 2. Simulations were conducted by experienced CFD analysts with domain knowledge in cardiovascular device modeling. Internal peer review of simulation setup was performed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required for MRL 2; default level 1 is acceptable.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty (turbulence model selection, hemolysis power-law model coefficients) is not formally assessed at MRL 2. The k-omega SST turbulence model and Giersiepen hemolysis correlation were selected based on published literature recommendations for similar pump geometries."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required for MRL 2; default level 1 is acceptable.",
      "rationale": "Formal uncertainty quantification of model inputs is not required at MRL 2. Blood analog fluid properties (viscosity, density) were taken from published FDA study specifications. Sensitivity to input variation was not formally quantified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required for MRL 2; default level 1 is acceptable.",
      "rationale": "Statistical characterization of test sample variability is not required at MRL 2. The FDA interlaboratory study used standardized bovine blood samples across participating laboratories; sample-to-sample variability was reported in the source publication."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
